pages.page_overview_summary: This sheet provides the foundation, floor, and column plan for the farm storage shed. It includes the layout of concrete footings and columns, as well as foundation walls. Top plate nailing details are also provided. The plan is essential for understanding the structural base of the building.

pages.general_notes_verbatim:
GENERAL NOTES
1. DESIGN AND CONSTRUCTION OF ALL WORK ON THIS PROJECT
SHALL COMPLY WITH THE LATEST EDITIONS OF THE FOLLOWING:
- ONTARIO BUILDING CODE
- NATIONAL BUILDING CODE
- CSA STANDARDS
2. THE ENGINEER SHALL BE NOTIFIED OF ANY DISCREPANCIES BY
THE CONTRACTOR PRIOR TO PROCEEDING WITH THE WORK.
3. ALL DIMENSIONS TO BE VERIFIED ON SITE.
4. ALL MATERIALS TO BE NEW AND FREE FROM DEFECTS.
5. ALL WORK TO BE PERFORMED IN A WORKMANLIKE MANNER.
6. THE CONTRACTOR SHALL COORDINATE THE WORK OF ALL
TRADES AND ENSURE THAT ALL OPENINGS, INSERTS, AND
EMBEDDED ITEMS ARE PROVIDED AS REQUIRED.
7. THE CONTRACTOR SHALL PROVIDE ADEQUATE TEMPORARY BRACING AND
SHORING TO ENSURE THE STABILITY OF THE STRUCTURE DURING
CONSTRUCTION.
8. THE CONTRACTOR SHALL BE RESPONSIBLE FOR THE DESIGN AND
CONSTRUCTION OF ALL TEMPORARY WORKS.
9. ALL WORK TO BE CARRIED OUT IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE
CONTRACT DOCUMENTS AND THE ENGINEER'S INSTRUCTIONS.
10. THE CONTRACTOR SHALL PROVIDE THE ENGINEER WITH
SUFFICIENT NOTICE TO INSPECT THE WORK AT THE FOLLOWING
STAGES:
- FOOTINGS (PRIOR TO POURING CONCRETE)
- STRUCTURAL FRAMING
- FINAL INSPECTION (PRIOR TO OCCUPANCY)
EXCAVATION AND BACKFILL:
1. REMOVE ALL TOPSOIL AND UNSUITABLE MATERIAL FROM BELOW BUILDING.
2. ALLOW FOR ADEQUATE DRAINAGE AWAY FROM BUILDING.
3. BACKFILL TO BE COMPACTED TO 98% STANDARD PROCTOR DENSITY.
4. EXCAVATE FOR FOOTINGS.
5. BACKFILL TO BE PLACED IN LAYERS NOT EXCEEDING 150 MM IN THICKNESS.
6. BACKFILL TO BE COMPACTED TO 95% STANDARD PROCTOR DENSITY.
7. BACKFILL TO BE FREE OF ORGANIC MATERIAL AND DEBRIS.
8. BACKFILL TO BE PLACED AND COMPACTED IN A MANNER THAT WILL
NOT DAMAGE THE STRUCTURE.
